.TH "snd_ctl_add_vmaster_hook" 9 "snd_ctl_add_vmaster_hook" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_ctl_add_vmaster_hook \- Add a hook to a vmaster control
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_ctl_add_vmaster_hook
.BI "(struct snd_kcontrol *kcontrol "  ","
.BI "void (*hook)(void *private_data, int) "  ","
.BI "void *private_data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kcontrol" 12
vmaster kctl element
.IP "hook" 12
the hook function
.IP "private_data" 12
the private_data pointer to be saved
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Adds the given hook to the vmaster control element so that it's called
at each time when the value is changed.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero.
